@page
@model sample_1.Pages.aboutusModel
@{
	ViewData["Title"] = "About Us";
}
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/aboutus.css" />
</head>
<section id="about-us">
    <div class="about-container">
        <h2>ABOUT US</h2>
        <p>Welcome to our Course Registration platform. Our legacy is built on academic excellence, innovation, and community engagement. Our dedicated faculty, staff, and resources support your journey toward achieving your goals.</p>

        <h3>Our Mission</h3>
        <p>To empower students through exceptional education, innovative learning, and personal growth. We foster academic excellence, diversity, equity, and inclusion, driving community engagement and global understanding.</p>

        <h3>Why Choose Us?</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Wide range of courses tailored to your needs.</li>
            <li>Experienced instructors with industry expertise.</li>
            <li>Flexible learning options for busy schedules.</li>
            <li>Supportive community of learners.</li>
            <li>Flexible learning formats and affordable education.</li>
            <li>Modern infrastructure enhancing learning and engaging extracurricular activities.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Our Story</h3>
        <p>Founded in 1837, MCC is one of Asia's oldest extant colleges. The college is affiliated to the University of Madras but functions as an autonomous institution from its main campus in Tambaram, Chennai. MCC has 38 departments, including day and evening streams, with over 8500 students.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <div class="gallery-container">
        <div class="gallery-item">
            <img src="images/campus2.jpeg" alt="Campus">
            <div class="gallery-content">
                <h3>Campus</h3>
                <p>The 365-acre (1.48 km2) campus is known for its flora and fauna, notably deer and rare trees. The college is distinguished by a lake on campus.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery-item">
            <img src="images/Andersonhall.png" alt="Anderson Hall">
            <div class="gallery-content">
                <h3>Anderson Hall</h3>
                <p>MCC's largest auditorium, named after its founder Rev. John Anderson, was built in anticipation of the third World Missionary Conference in 1938.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery-item">
            <img src="images/Quadrangle.png" alt="MCC Quadrangle">
            <div class="gallery-content">
                <h3>MCC Quadrangle</h3>
                <p>The quadrangle or diamond in front of the main building is used for large student gatherings like the annual Deepwoods cultural festival.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery-item">
            <img src="images/gutters.png" alt="Cafeteria and Gutters">
            <div class="gallery-content">
                <h3>Cafeteria and Gutters</h3>
                <p>Popular hangouts for intellectual conversations and the birthplace of artistic initiatives by students.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery-item">
            <img src="images/Mc.png" alt="Macphail's Arts Centre">
            <div class="gallery-content">
                <h3>Macphail's Arts Centre</h3>
                <p>The Fine Arts Centre, named after J.R. Macphail, is the venue for department cultural events.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery-item">
            <img src="images/Pavillion.jpg" alt="Sportsfields and Pavilion">
            <div class="gallery-content">
                <h3>Sportsfields and Pavilion</h3>
                <p>The campus has several sports fields and facilities, including cricket, football, tennis, basketball, and more.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery-item">
            <img src="images/Miller memorial lib.jpeg" alt="Miller Memorial Library">
            <div class="gallery-content">
                <h3>Miller Memorial Library</h3>
                <p>An extensive library established in 1863, now digitized and equipped with facilities for visually challenged students.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="gallery-item">
            <img src="images/Deepwoods.jpeg" alt="Deepwoods Festival">
            <div class="gallery-content">
                <h3>Deepwoods</h3>
                <p>Deepwoods is MCC's intercollegiate fest featuring diverse cultural events like dancing, singing, and more over three days.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
